MESSAGE: 2002 chevy camaro z28 - 35 year aniversary edition - 6-speed - 77500mi#most of these are beaten up. this one is not. it is in great shape; both mechanically and cosmetically. i know that pictures often hide imperfections; but this one looks as good or better in person. it is damn near perfect. i have owned it since 2006 as a summer car which is why i only put 40;000 miles on it in 11 years. it was always garaged and; of course; i always had another car for winter and other uses when i didnt like to drive the z28.#the only upgrades that were done in 2005 were gears (to 3.73); borla cat-back exhaust (passes emissions and has a pleasant note that is deeper than stock - far from obnoxious); and slp intake.#these are getting rare. ones in such good condition are exceptionally rare. i have always gotten compliments for color and now more and more for the shape it is in. this car is guaranteed to turn more heads than newer camaros that you can see all over the place now. horse-power is not quite as high as the newer muscle cars; however even with its 310hp; upgraded gears and less weight it runs about as strong as newer 400hp cars.#in other words; there is no way you can get such a solid car that is as fun/cool as this one for nearly as little money as i am asking. another thing is that these can keep their value or go up if they are well kept and not driven too much. newer ones depreciate a lot; so why would you want to buy a 5 year old (for example) for $20;000 and have it be worth $12;000 in a few years; while you can have this one for around $10;000 and either sell it for about same in a few years or keep it longer and probably make money selling it at some point.#so; you may wonder; why am i selling it then. the truth is i dont really need to sell it - i just have too many cars and not as much garage space to keep them; so since ive had this one for 11 years i am ready to part with. i also dont have enough chance to drive it and i hate seeing a car like this just sit there and not be enjoyed by someone. so; now that i have talked my wife into letting me sell it (as she is still kind of in love with it) i want to offer it before she changes her mind.#i do not need help selling the car!#no low ball offers - you will waste your breath/keyboard/phone/trip!#i will let you drive it but only if i judge that you are serious.#email (through craigslist) is best way to get in touch with me. if you are serious we can arrange to talk ...#the car is located in rockton il !

MESSAGE: $7900 or will consider trades for a motorcycle (a sport tourer with hard cases) of an approximately equal value.#you will never get more fast car for less money than this; and if i still had any interest in fast cars i would never sell it at this price. the first person who actually realizes that a fully built car with $16;000 just in performance parts alone is up for sale for $7900; gets the car. and ive done both buyer and seller a favor by listing the lowest price. $7900. thats it; no bargaining.#its an lt1 engine; stroked and bored to 396ci and supercharged to 11psi. it is driveable on the street and it will beat anything on the road except something like a new z06 or a top of the line porsche. and it would still give any of them a run for it at that. its fully built from front to back and almost everything on it has less than 3000 miles of use. ive also only taken it to a track one time; and it was an 1/8th mile track so i dont have a quarter mile time; but i do have a dyno chart; and it made 605 hp at the wheels with the old camshaft. ive put a more civilized cam in there since then; and it probably makes about 550 now; but it drives much better. it has a stiff suspension which consists of adjustable shocks; eibach springs; and panhard bar; along with aftermarket rear struts. also a stiff frame due to kenny bell subframe connectors. its a forged motor; of course; with four bolt mains; callies crank; eagle h-beam rods; and custom ross pistons. 8.75 compression and 11 psi with liquid intercooler and vortech s-trim. transmission built by six speeds inc. for $2;000; new clutch; new pressure plate; new flywheel insert; 12 bolt rear with eaton positraction best of everything option. what this means is; nothing is going to break; and if you know the 4th gen camaro/firebird you know that these are all the best parts you can get. it also has an electric cutout: push the switch to open it up and it sounds like something escaped from a zoo that has no place on a public road; but close it up and you can leave a neighborhood late on a week night without waking anyone up. it has a fuel pressure gauge; boost gauge; air/fuel gauge reading off a wideband o2; and an innovate motorsports logging system; so you can plug in a laptop to the usb and log tps; revs; air/fuel; etc. also new dual walbro fuel pumps; etc; etc; etc.#new o2s; new wheel bearings; new brakes; new tps; new iac valve; new optispark; new fuel filter; new tires; new tie rods; new alternator; new ignition coil; new clutch master cylinder; new oil pump.#the body could use some paint--you can see the clear coat coming off the hood-- and theres some cosmetic stuff to do to the interior. ive focused on all the working parts and never got to the cosmetics. the slot you can see in the custom aluminum dash is for an audio receiver which i never got to putting in.#i got married a year ago; and i dont have the zeal for working on cars now that i used to anyway. i have enough other stuff to keep up with. in closing; everything is basically new. nothing should be breaking anytime soon; no matter what you do with it. it was built solid and built right.#and; i will make sure that i take this ad down as soon as it sells. so if this ad is still up; the car is still for sale. feel free to contact me if you want to take a look at it.

TITLE: 95 camaro 3400 built engine; 2400 stall; 3.73 gears; line locks & more
ATTR: condition: good#cylinders: 6 cylinders#drive: rwd#fuel: gas#odometer: 158300#paint color: black#size: mid-size#title status: clean#transmission: automatic#type: coupe
MESSAGE: heres the story on this car; my buddy built it around 10 years ago with everything new. (i have a massive stack of receipts in a folder) he did pretty much everything you would do to a v8. subframe connectors; tunnel brace; traction bars; hotchkis front strut tower brace; suspension techniques sway bars; bilstein shocks; lowering springs. entire suspension and wheel wells were sanded down; painted; replaced with energy suspension bushings. steel braided brake lines; rear disc brake conversion. all brakes are new. ive never drove another camaro that handled like this before. you point where you want to go and it does it. very little sway and smooth on the street.#problem was the car had a bad harness and he could never get it run. engine is bore .030 over w/ v8 valve springs for a custom comp cam. he took it out when it didnt run and trashed it he was so mad. i still have the cam card because he had a jet performance ecu made for it. 2400 stall torque converter; built trans w shift kit to handle spray and rear end w/ 3.73 gears. car was originally built for 150 shot of nos to be a fun sleeper car that he could drive to work every day. never put the system on it since it he couldnt figure out the electrical issue. its really just a smooth cruiser that handles great with out spray and should last a really long time. its mechanically a rebuilt car. only thing is the steering rack is still stock and has a slow leak. its the only thing i ever check and top off.#i picked it up when i blew the motor on my race car that i was also using as a daily at the time; paid all the tags; smogged it; got the a/c going. replaced the engine harness and ignition control module. new fuel pump. a lot of the sensors were replaced so almost everything is new and reliable. ive put over 3k miles on it so far and only changed the oil once. put in a nice pioneer head unit; blue tooth; ipod capable; headphone jack; orion front speakers and pioneer back speakers. new 17x9.5 wheels and 255/40/17 tires. i personally spent $4500 so far. my friend had spent well over $10k before that. bottom line i got my s2000 track car running plus a sti daily and little parking where i live to keep it. car would be great for kid but i dont have one of those to keep it for either lol.#im currently running the stock ecu. msd coils; wires; pace setter headers and custom exhaust w/ high flow cat so its all smog legal. i always get asked if i have an ls or lt. i just replaced the egr valve but it was clogged passageways so the car comes w a spare egr; oem coils. has a k&n stock replacement filter. the injectors are brand new. i have a brand new fuel pressure regulator but it doesnt need it so thats in the box. the entire a/c system was replaced and done right. blows as cold as new. car has custom gauges so some of the needles are not perfectly accurate so he added a dual pillar pod with auto meter oil pressure and coolant gauges. they are on a separate switch so they dont have to be lit up at night when your light are on. car does have line locks which are fun. the fans are on a switch too so you can cool off when ever you want. it also has a transcooler installed. my friend said he still has 1000hp axles at his house i might be able to pick up and throw in. i just dont have a truck to get them. drivers door window was converted to power windows; the switch and kit is there for the passenger side if you want to finish it. right now the passenger is standard manual window. new shocks for the rear hatch. new battery.#im sure there is a lot more. you can go through the receipts and drive it to see how it drives. im in no rush to sell or get super low balled on it; i dont need any trades or more cars lol. any questions; feel free to ask. thanks.

MESSAGE: up for sale is a one of a kind camaro z/28. the sub model was the 1s/c (stripped coupe) meaning manual everything; but has t-tops. the car not only has a sleek navy blue metallic paint; it has the heart of a c5 corvette z06. to specify; the car is far from stock. this camaro used to be a bone stock ls1 automatic car; that was until the previous owner wanted a manual. so it was swapped with an ls6 (still 5.7l) and a t56 6speed manual transmission. before you ask if the whole drivetrain has been swapped; the answer is yes. i have more receipts than i know what to do with for this car. the camaro was also fitted with a s60 strange performance rear end (3.54 gears) but can have higher gears without shimming the pumpkin. you could be cruising 80mph; in 6th gear; and be right under 2;000 rpm. one thing i will elaborate about the drivetrain; the engine internals are stock. the engine was not a remanufactured; it was a new engine from weir chevrolet in red bud; illinois. the transmission has been gone through with aftermarket heavier duty shaft seals; carbon fiber synchronizers; synchromesh fluid only; stage ii monster clutch (standard with cars that have the ls7 engine). i know the transmission description is vague; but like i said; there are so many reciepts its hard to list all the specific parts in one ad; and i havent talked about the bolt on parts yet! along with the drivetrain; there have been a few bolt on aftermlarket parts added as well. american racing long tube headers; high flow catalytic converters to a y pipe; stock gmmg exhaust chambers; 38 fuel injectors; c6 rims (275x17) tires 70% tread left front and back. rksports duck lip spoiler; handle shift knob/stick shaft; led low beam headlights from opt7; duralast gold battery; slp cold air intake/ ss hood with ram air ducts; aftermarket oil catch can; paint match valve#cover; power steering pulley; other small engine accents. i will add the the car does not currently have the a/c hooked up. the condeser; compressor; and lines i have that can come with the car. most times the car has a small grind in reverse if you try to throw it into that gear too quickly; you have to take it slow into reverse. couldnt explain why; but the previous owner didnt install the reverse synchro. but there is well over $20;000 worth of new parts on this car all with less that 40;000 miles on them. the car has no blemishes physically or internally; this is a great car if you like to take it to shows and cruise on a sunday evening; or take it to the track on a friday night; this car can do it all.i have had it on a dyno; makes 386hp/375tq to the rear wheels. this car has been a wonderful car; i drive it everyday; unless its raining. interior is in immaculate condition; as well as the underbody. come check the car out; let it speak for itself along with the 50 receipts for the partsdone from credible performance shops. also has 15% tint on the sides; rear; and brow on the windshield.#will consider trades for possible truck; would like to be 4x4 and diesel fuel. would look at 7.3 and 6.0 power stroke; must be bulletproofed if its a 6.0. and a cummins; with a manual trans only.#text justin: 314; 7.5.0; 0173
